content: Had a coffee chat with a mentor about past trading failures. The conversation was eye-opening—got some new strategies to try out.
Presented my initial AI market analysis concept at the firm. Got some constructive feedback, but they're intrigued. Time to refine and pivot.
Dug into some historical trading data for my AI project. The patterns are fascinating, but making sense of it all is like solving a Rubik's cube blindfolded.
Celebrating a small win: my Rust script for blockchain simulation passed all the initial tests. Feeling like a kid who just built his first Lego set.
The blockchain study group is taking off. We're planning a hackathon. Maybe my AI market analysis could be our project?
Had an intense brainstorming session with the group. We're aligning my AI project with the hackathon theme. The simulation feels like it's glitching—too much excitement.
Took a mentor's advice and started journaling my trading decisions. It's helping me see where I went wrong and how to fix it. Progress feels slow, but steady.
Spent the last few days refining my AI model. It's now predicting market trends with 60% accuracy. Not perfect, but I'm getting there.
Just received an email from the firm. They want a deeper dive into my blockchain project. This could be my chance to lead something big.
Had a late-night coding session. My quantum-resistant blockchain algorithm is shaping up, but there's still much to do. Coffee is my co-pilot.
Joined a virtual conference on blockchain security. Learning a ton, networking with experts. This could be the missing piece for my project.
Pitched my AI market analysis side project to a startup incubator. They're interested in a follow-up meeting. Feels like the stars are aligning.
